rComments: Stats is hard but Geoff makes it way easier! The course can feel overwhelming at times but he is very accessible outside of class and his lectures and slides are easy to understand. I didn't like the course but I really liked Geoff's teaching style and accessibility.

McCarney is the best professor I have ever had at the University of Ottawa. He is such a caring prof and will answer any questions you might have and ensure that you understand! If you have him for stats you are lucky! This was the class I was the most stressed about in my program but because of this prof I enjoyed the class a lot!

If you have to take Stats, please take it with Geoff! He is amazing and really cares about his students! I honestly thought I was going to fail this class, but finished with a really good mark thanks to Geoff! P.S: Don't buy the textbook you wont need it for anything.

Prof McCarney is absolutely amazing. He's obviously very knowledgable in stats and effectively portrayed the subject matter in ways that students (who generally hate stats) could understand. He was always in good spirits & always made sure we were comfortable with a concept before moving on. If you need to take stats, I strongly recommend this prof

I don't normally write reviews for professors, but professor McCarney is an exception. I never expected to do well in stats, but he genuinely wants his students to do well and is always available to help. I would HIGHLY recommend professor McCarney for stats, especially if you haven't taken math since high school. You will not find a better prof.
Really good stats prof! I would highly recommend taking his class if you have to take stats. H
